          "text": "# Plan: parallel `message_id → line ranges` attestation in git-ai\n\n## Context\n\ngit-ai records AI authorship in the authorship note's NOTE CONTENT block at conversation granularity (e.g. `c249********1004 1-11,16-27`). The user is building a research tool that needs **per-line message granularity** — for each commit, the latest user message that edited each line.\n\nCHEs already carry message-level `prompt_id`, but their line numbers are stored in checkpoint coordinates that go stale on rebase/squash, so `line_history` (which walks CHEs) becomes unreliable. We need a **parallel attestation stream** keyed by `user_prompt_id` (message id), in commit-final coordinates.\n\nUser has chosen:\n- **Q1 = (a)** — persist the new stream **per-checkpoint** on `WorkingLogEntry`, mirroring the conversation-level stream's persistence pattern.\n- **Q2 = (a)** — Human checkpoints **drop** the message_id from any line they touch (mirrors the existing conversation-level behavior of dropping pure-human-overridden lines from the attestation).\n\n**Out of scope for this plan**: rebase/squash propagation. Schema is designed to be forward-compatible with `merge_attributions_favoring_first` in `virtual_attribution.rs:2074`, but threading the message stream through rebase paths is a follow-up.\n\n## Schema additions\n\n### `src/authorship/attribution_tracker.rs`\nAdd char-level and line-level mirror structs:\n```rust\npub struct MessageAttribution {\n    pub start: usize,\n    pub end: usize,\n    pub message_id: Option<String>,   // None for human-edited regions\n    pub ts: u128,\n}\n\npub struct MessageLineAttribution {\n    pub start_line: u32,\n    pub end_line: u32,\n    pub message_id: Option<String>,\n}\n```\n\n### `src/authorship/working_log.rs`\nAdd two parallel fields on `WorkingLogEntry`, both `#[serde(default, skip_serializing_if = ...)]` for backward compatibility:\n```rust\npub message_attributions: Vec<MessageAttribution>,\npub message_line_attributions: Vec<MessageLineAttribution>,\n```\n\n### `src/authorship/authorship_log_serialization.rs`\nAdd a parallel collection on `AuthorshipLog`:\n```rust\npub struct AuthorshipLog {\n    pub attestations: Vec<FileAttestation>,            // existing — untouched\n    pub message_attestations: Vec<FileAttestation>,    // new — same struct, different keys\n    pub metadata: AuthorshipMetadata,\n}\n```\nThe `AttestationEntry { hash, line_ranges }` struct is reused — `hash` just stores message UUIDs instead of conversation hashes.\n\n## Per-checkpoint flow (in `commands/checkpoint.rs`)\n\n### `build_previous_file_state_maps` (`:1649-1674`)\nCarry forward the message char attributions alongside the existing ones:\n```rust\nPreviousFileState {\n    blob_sha: ...,\n    attributions: ...,\n    message_attributions: entry.message_attributions.clone(),  // new\n}\n```\n\n### `make_entry_for_file` (`:2156-2248`)\nAfter the existing conversation-stream pass, add a parallel pass:\n```rust\nlet current_message_id = checkpoint.user_prompt_id.clone();  // None for Human checkpoints\nlet new_message_attrs = tracker.update_message_attributions_for_checkpoint(\n    previous_content, content, &prev_message_attrs,\n    current_message_id.as_deref(), ts, is_ai_checkpoint,\n)?;\nlet message_line_attrs = message_attributions_to_line_attributions(\n    &new_message_attrs, content,\n);\nentry.message_attributions = new_message_attrs;\nentry.message_line_attributions = message_line_attrs;\n```\n\n### New methods on `AttributionTracker`\n- `update_message_attributions_for_checkpoint(...)` — structurally identical to `update_attributions_for_checkpoint` (`:568+`), running the same imara-diff projection but stamping `message_id: Option<String>` instead of `author_id: String`. For `current_message_id == None` (human checkpoints), it stamps `None` on newly-edited regions; for AI checkpoints, it stamps `Some(user_prompt_id)`. Existing message_ids on preserved regions pass through unchanged.\n- `message_attributions_to_line_attributions(...)` — line-merge sweep mirroring `attributions_to_line_attributions` (`:2003-2077`), merging consecutive lines that share the same `message_id`. Drops lines whose merged `message_id` is `None`.\n\n## Aggregation (in `virtual_attribution.rs`)\n\n### `VirtualAttributions` struct\nAdd a new field:\n```rust\npub message_attributions: HashMap<String, Vec<MessageLineAttribution>>,\n```\n\n### `from_just_working_log` (`:313-480`)\nInside the per-checkpoint entry loop (around `:418-459`), after `attributions.insert(file, (char, line))`, also:\n```rust\nself.message_attributions.insert(entry.file.clone(), entry.message_line_attributions.clone());\n```\nLast checkpoint per file wins — same overwrite semantics as the existing stream, which is correct because the latest `message_line_attributions` is already cumulative (forward-projected through every prior checkpoint at checkpoint creation time).\n\n### `to_authorship_log` (`:988-1076`)\nAfter the existing per-`author_id` grouping loop (`:1010-1072`), add a parallel loop on `self.message_attributions`:\n```rust\nfor (file_path, msg_line_attrs) in &self.message_attributions {\n    let mut message_ranges: HashMap<String, Vec<(u32, u32)>> = HashMap::new();\n    for la in msg_line_attrs {\n        let Some(mid) = &la.message_id else { continue };  // honor Q2=a: drop human-edited\n        message_ranges.entry(mid.clone()).or_default()\n            .push((la.start_line, la.end_line));\n    }\n    // sort + merge adjacent ranges, build AttestationEntry, push into authorship_log.message_attestations\n}\n```\n\n## Note format — duplicate section after JSON metadata\n\nThe user wants the existing attestation block left alone in shape and position, with the message attestation as a duplicate of the same `<file>\\n  <hash> <ranges>` format. Place it **after** the JSON metadata, separated by a new `---` divider:\n\n```\nvoting-group.controller.ts\n  c249********1004 1-11,16-27\n---\n{ json metadata ... }\n---\nvoting-group.controller.ts\n  4e24dfe8-9cee-4798-b480-43045643743f 1-11\n  e1613b9c-5784-4064-85d0-b2262764a3df 12-15\n  fae25b8a-3979-4797-a422-780ecca2d544 16-27\n```\n\n### `serialize_to_string` (`:212-243`)\nAfter the existing pre-divider attestation loop and JSON section, append:\n```rust\noutput.push_str(\"\\n---\\n\");\nfor file_attestation in &self.message_attestations {\n    output.push_str(&maybe_quote(&file_attestation.file_path));\n    output.push('\\n');\n    for entry in &file_attestation.entries {\n        output.push_str(\"  \");\n        output.push_str(&entry.hash);\n        output.push(' ');\n        output.push_str(&format_line_ranges(&entry.line_ranges));\n        output.push('\\n');\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### `deserialize_from_string` (`:255-277`)\nReplace the single `---` split with a multi-divider split:\n- Lines before the **first** `---` → `attestations` (unchanged behavior).\n- Lines between first and second `---` → JSON `metadata` (unchanged behavior).\n- Lines after the **second** `---` (if present) → parse via the same `parse_attestation_section` into `message_attestations`. Absent second divider = empty `message_attestations` (backward-compatible with old notes).\n\n`parse_attestation_section` (`:637-699`) is reused as-is for the new block.\n\n## New `message_history` command\n\nNew file `src/commands/message_history.rs`, mirroring `commands/line_history.rs`:\n- Inputs: `<file>`, `<line>`, optional `--commit <sha>` (default HEAD).\n- Walk `git log -L<line>,<line>:<file>` to find commits that touched the line. Reuse `git_log_line_history` from `commands/line_history.rs`.\n- For each commit:\n  - Read the authorship note via `get_reference_as_authorship_log_v3` (existing utility).\n  - Find the entry in `note.message_attestations[file]` whose ranges contain `<line>`.\n  - That entry's `hash` is the `message_id`.\n  - Look up the message text by scanning `note.metadata.prompts.<conv>.messages` for `Message::User { id: Some(this_msg_id), .. }`.\n  - Output a row: `(commit_sha, message_id, message_text)`. If no message attestation contains the line (e.g. human last touched it, or the note pre-dates this feature), output `(commit_sha, null, null)`.\n- Output formats: text (default) and JSON (`--format=json`).\n\n## Critical files to modify\n\n- `src/authorship/attribution_tracker.rs` — `MessageAttribution`, `MessageLineAttribution` structs; `update_message_attributions_for_checkpoint`; `message_attributions_to_line_attributions`.\n- `src/authorship/working_log.rs` — new fields on `WorkingLogEntry`.\n- `src/commands/checkpoint.rs` — `PreviousFileState` carry-forward; `make_entry_for_file` parallel pass.\n- `src/authorship/virtual_attribution.rs` — `VirtualAttributions.message_attributions`; `from_just_working_log` checkpoint-walk update; `to_authorship_log` parallel grouping.\n- `src/authorship/authorship_log_serialization.rs` — `AuthorshipLog.message_attestations`; serializer + deserializer updates.\n- `src/commands/message_history.rs` — new file.\n- Wherever commands are registered (likely `src/commands/mod.rs` and `src/main.rs`/`src/bin/`) — wire up the new subcommand.\n\n## Existing utilities to reuse (don't reimplement)\n\n- `update_attributions` / `update_attributions_for_checkpoint` (`attribution_tracker.rs:550, :568`) — the imara-diff projection engine. The new tracker method has the same shape.\n- The line-merging sweep in `attributions_to_line_attributions_for_checkpoint` (`attribution_tracker.rs:2010+`).\n- `format_line_ranges` / `parse_line_ranges` and `parse_attestation_section` (`authorship_log_serialization.rs`).\n- `AttestationEntry`, `FileAttestation`, `LineRange` structs.\n- `git_log_line_history` and the `--format` plumbing in `commands/line_history.rs`.\n- `get_reference_as_authorship_log_v3` for reading notes.\n\n## Verification\n\n1. **Build**: `cargo build` from `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai`.\n2. **Unit tests**: extend `attribution_tracker.rs` test module to cover:\n   - `update_message_attributions_for_checkpoint` carrying old message_ids through preserved regions and stamping new ones on edits.\n   - `update_message_attributions_for_checkpoint(..., None, ...)` setting message_id to None on edited regions.\n   - `message_attributions_to_line_attributions` dropping `None` lines and merging same-`message_id` consecutive lines.\n3. **Integration scenario** in `git-ai-testing/`, replicating the voting-group log:\n   - Cursor session: create file (msg M1) → checkpoint 1.\n   - Same session: edit one line (msg M2) → checkpoint 2.\n   - Human edit (no message) on a different line → checkpoint 3.\n   - Commit. Inspect note: `git notes --ref refs/notes/git-ai show HEAD`.\n   - Confirm: existing attestation block has conversation hash with M1∪M2 ranges; new block has M1 with non-overlapping ranges + M2 with the edited line; the human-edited line appears under no message id.\n4. **New command**: `git ai message_history voting-group.controller.ts <line>` for several `<line>` values; confirm correct latest message per commit and that the human-touched line returns null.\n5. **Regression**: `cargo test` passes; existing line_history command and conversation attestation outputs are byte-identical for unchanged fixtures.\n\n## Open items for implementation phase (verify before coding)\n\n- Read the body of `update_attributions` (`attribution_tracker.rs:550+`) to confirm whether the message-stream variant should be a separate function (cleaner) or a generic-over-author-type rewrite (less duplication). Default to a separate function for clarity unless the bodies are trivial to share.\n- Confirm whether any existing consumer outside the codebase relies on the note ending exactly at the JSON's closing `}` (which the trailing `---\\n<message attestation>` would change). If so, gate the new block behind a serializer flag.\n- Confirm `from_working_log_snapshot` and `from_working_log_for_commit` (sister methods to `from_just_working_log` at `virtual_attribution.rs:484`, `:797`, `:885`) need the same checkpoint-walk update.\n",
